        <name>rfcomm</name>
        <qualifiedname>bt_goep_transport_rfcomm_server::rfcomm</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
<para>RFCOMM server for GOEP v1.1. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>The <ref refid="structbt__goep__transport__rfcomm__server_1adaa1fb6c58cdb28560e3b4be272ae94d" kindref="member">bt_goep_transport_rfcomm_server::rfcomm</ref> is used to register a rfcomm server.</para>
<para>The <ref refid="structbt__rfcomm__server_1a30b22ea64c0fdd7130e8aaa79519e776" kindref="member">bt_rfcomm_server::channel</ref> needs to be passed with a pre-set channel (not recommended however), Or give a value <computeroutput>0</computeroutput> to make the channel be auto-allocated when <ref refid="group__bt__goep__transport__rfcomm_1ga781dc33ffa086753319c84f59b8e977f" kindref="member">bt_goep_transport_rfcomm_server_register</ref> is called. The <ref refid="structbt__rfcomm__server_1ac08708bb8161f787737962f62d3c003f" kindref="member">bt_rfcomm_server::accept</ref> should be not used by GOEP application, and instead the <ref refid="structbt__goep__transport__rfcomm__server_1a66c433a47c20018f9f0a018b4fbc8048" kindref="member">bt_goep_transport_rfcomm_server::accept</ref> should be used. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
        <location file="zephyr/bluetooth/classic/goep.h" line="139" column="23" bodyfile="zephyr/bluetooth/classic/goep.h" bodystart="139" bodyend="-1"/>
